docs.lead_paragraph: PATERSON, N.J., April 1 -- A double tragedy was enacted at Lakeview, a suburb of Paterson, this morning, a young man and his bride ending their lives by taking carbolic acid. The victims were Thomas S. Stothard, twenty-one years old, of Hazel Street, Lakeview, and his wife. Louisa C. Stothard, twenty-three years old.

headline.main: DOUBLE SUICIDE IN PATERSON.; Young Stothard and His Bride Apparently Despaired of Getting Parental Forgiveness.
